<HEADLINE> A's Giambi Leaves Game With Injury  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   OAKLAND, Calif. (AP) -- Oakland first baseman Jason Giambi left
Monday night's game against the Cleveland Indians after batting in
the third inning because of a strained left shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   The All-Star, who singled in the first innings, was hurt on a
check swing in the third. He grounded out to shortstop, and was
then replaced in the field by his younger brother, Jeremy Giambi.
</P>
<P>
   Jason Giambi has 30 home runs and 101 RBIs.
</P>
</TEXT>
