<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Expos Activate Cabrera From DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- The Montreal Expos activated shortstop Orlando
Cabrera from the 15-day disabled list Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Cabrera, who completed a four-game rehab assignment with
Triple-A Ottawa Monday night, will join the Expos for their series
opener against San Francisco after missing the past month due to a
separated right shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Cabrera was hitting .243 with eight homers and 34 RBIs for the
Expos this season when he injured himself while diving for a ball
on July 14 at Tropicana Field, during an 8-5 loss to the Tampa Bay
Devil Rays.
</P>
<P>
   Shortstop Tomas De La Rosa was optioned to Ottawa following
Montreal's 4-3 loss to Colorado Monday night.
</P>
</TEXT>
