<HEADLINE> 15 Injured in Baltimore Bar Crash  </HEADLINE>
By SHEILA HOTCHKIN
<TEXT>
<P>
   CARNEY, Md. (AP) -- A speeding car slammed into the side of a
crowded Baltimore County bar Monday night, sending at least 15
people to the hospital, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The car lost control, struck another vehicle and crashed into
the wall of the Firehouse Tavern about 10:30 p.m. The bar, in a
northeastern suburb of Baltimore, was packed with patrons.
</P>
<P>
   The car's three occupants and 12 bar patrons were taken to the
hospital, said Lt. Minda Foxwell of the Baltimore County Police
Department.
</P>
<P>
   Four with more serious injuries were taken to University of
Maryland Shock Trauma, including two of the car's occupants, she
said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said the vehicle matched the description of one they had
been chasing moments earlier following a shooting at Skateland, a
roller-skating rink in the nearby suburb of Towson. The brief
pursuit had been called off because the fleeing car was going too
fast, Foxwell said.
</P>
<P>
   Kevin Mack was stopped outside the Firehouse Tavern en route to
work when he saw the speeding car, its lights off, ''literally
airborne.''
</P>
<P>
   ''I kind of froze because he was heading directly for my
vehicle,'' Mack told WJZ-TV. The oncoming vehicle skidded, hit the
back of Mack's car and spun left, heading for the bar. ''Within a
split-second it went right through the building,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
