<HEADLINE> Dow Slips 32; Nasdaq Drops 5  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 32
points in today's early going. Losing issues on the New York Stock
Exchange hold a 9-7 lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off five points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down two points.
</P>
<P>
   Wall Street will get retail news this morning, with earnings
reports from several major retailers including Home Depot, J.C.
Penney and Target.
</P>
<P>
   As far as economic news, the Federal Reserve reports that
industrial production rose 0.4 percent in July, in line with
expectations.
</P>
<P>
   Going into today's session, the Dow had risen in ten of the
previous eleven sessions.
</P>
