<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 75; Nasdaq Sllps 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned lower Tuesday, as investors sold
off blue chips after three straight winning sessions. Technology
issues slipped.
</P>
<P>
   In early afternoon trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was down 75.45 to 11,100.69, after a 148-point
surge on Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was down 4.57 to 1,486.99. The
Nasdaq composite index was down 3.24 to 3,846.45.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts said profit taking was largely responsible for Dow's
drop. The Dow had risen in recent days amid optimism that the
Federal Reserve would leave interest rates unchanged at its meeting
next week.
</P>
<P>
   Retailers, which would gain from a stable interest rate
environment, helped pull the market down.
</P>
<P>
   Dow component Home Depot, which met Wall Street forecasts, fell
$5.065 to $54.375 after a big run-up the past two weeks. Some
analysts were concerned the retailer did not beat their estimates.
</P>
<P>
   J.C. Penney dropped $1.875 to $16.063 after reporting that its
second-quarter operating profit dropped 90 percent due to lower
sales and price cuts.
</P>
<P>
   Drugmakers, which have benefitted from many investors' turn
toward defensive stocks that can better withstand an economic
downturn, were mixed.
</P>
<P>
   Bristol-Myers Squibb, which made a legal maneuver Tuesday that
seems to temporarily preserve its patent protection on its
blockbuster cancer drug Taxol, rose $3.123 to $53.75. Generic
drugmaker Ivax, which was poised to start making a cheaper, generic
Taxol, plunged $13.75 to $28.625.
</P>
<P>
   Among technology stocks, JDS Uniphase fell $2.75 to $117.50 and
Radio Shack dropped $3.875 to $65.125.
</P>
<P>
   On the economic front, the Federal Reserve said industrial
production rose 0.4 percent in July, in line with analysts'
expectations. The report contained little sign of inflation, which
should make investors more confident the central bank will leave
interest rates unchanged when it convenes next week.
</P>
<P>
   Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 7 to-5 margin on the
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 588.21 million
shares, up from Monday's pace.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index fell 3.15 to 511.33.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
</TEXT>
