<HEADLINE> American To Get Tests in Russia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Russian doctors have agreed to perform
additional tests on an imprisoned American at the request of the
doctor at the U.S. Embassy in Moscow, the State Department said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The American, Pennsylvania businessman Edmond Pope, has bone
cancer that is in remission. He was arrested four months ago on
charges of stealing military secrets.
</P>
