<HEADLINE> Jackie Kennedy's BMW up for auction  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WAINSCOTT, N.Y. (AP) - A blue and green BMW once owned by
Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis is to be auctioned for an estimated
$35,000 to $75,000, the auctioneer said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Mrs. Onassis drove the car, a Bavaria 3.0S four-door sedan with
a tan interior, from 1974 to 1992, said Xavier Meignan, president
of Finest Auctions, which will sell the vehicle.
</P>
