<HEADLINE> Mondale: Gore Needs To Be Gore  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Former Vice President Walter Mondale says Al
Gore must ''look within himself and be the best Al Gore he can be''
in his acceptance speech Thursday night -- and not try to outdo his
boss.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's not a night he should try to be a Clinton or somebody
else, but be confident in his own skills, his own directions,''
Mondale said in an interview on CNN.
