speech that brought the delegates to their feet cheering. And
Mondale said, ''I have never seen anybody better than Bill
Clinton.''
</P>
<P>
   But, the former veep to Jimmy Carter said Gore must leave his
own impression.
</P>
<P>
   ''This is his party and he can be himself,'' Mondale said. ''I
would play, if I were he, on my own strengths. Let the American
people see who I am.''
</P>
<P>
   Mondale lost his own presidential bid to Ronald Reagan in 1984.
