<HEADLINE> Expos' Irabu Has Surgery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONTREAL (AP) -- Montreal Expos pitcher Hideki Irabu had a bone
spur removed from his right elbow Tuesday during season-ending
surgery performed by orthopedic specialist Dr. James Andrews in
Birmingham, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   Irabu, acquired from the New York Yankees last Dec. 22, was
placed on the 15-day disabled list for the second time this season
on July 28, one day after making his first start in two months.
</P>
<P>
   Irabu was 2-5 with a 7.24 ERA in 11 starts for Montreal this
season.
</P>
<P>
   His recovery will take 2-3 months. Irabu is expected to be ready
for the beginning of training camp next February.
</P>
<P>
   Irabu, who had arthroscopic surgery on May 28 to repair torn
cartilage in his right knee, allowed five hits and three earned
runs in six innings in a 4-3 loss to the New York Mets at Shea
Stadium July 27.
</P>
</TEXT>
