<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-15 21:33 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> RETRANSMITTING to fix slug  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Text of speech by Nita M. Lowey, D-N.Y., at the
Democratic
National Convention in Los Angeles on Tuesday. Transcription by
eMediaMillWorks Inc.:
<TEXT>
<P>
   Today, I'm speaking about an issue of paramount importance to
every family in America - our right to choose.
</P>
<P>
   I won't mince words. This election will determine whether Roe v.
Wade continues to be the law of the land or whether we return to
the days of illegal abortion when thousands of women died.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1995, the right to choose has been under assault by our
opponents in Congress. They have forced almost 150 separate votes
to roll back our freedoms and impose government's will on women and
their families. They have pushed outright bans on medical
procedures, cuts in family planning and gag rules on doctors. And
they held our UN dues hostage to their extreme anti-choice views.
</P>
<P>
   At every turn, even when we try to reduce the need for abortions
through better access to contraception, they stand in the way. Only
the firm pro-choice commitment of this administration has kept the
right to choose intact.
</P>
<P>
   In this election, we risk losing a generation of progress, so we
owe it to the American people to be perfectly clear - make the
right choice today, or there's no choice tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   Al Gore, Joe Lieberman and the Democrats trust America's women
to make decisions for themselves. The Republican platform does not,
even in the wrenching case of rape or incest.
</P>
<P>
   Make the right choice today, or there's no choice tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   The next president will appoint as many as three or four Supreme
Court justices. It takes only one to tip the balance.
</P>
<P>
   Make the right choice today, or there's no choice tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   When we work together to improve access to contraception and
encourage responsible choices through education, Al Gore and Joe
Lieberman will stand proudly on that common ground. Our opponents
have not and will not.
</P>
<P>
   Make the right choice today, or there's no choice tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
   Al Gore and Joe Lieberman trust women, and they have a vision of
a world where every child is wanted, cared for and loved, where
women's lives matter, where the right to choose is safe and
accessible, where we focus on parenting, family planning and
halting the spread of HIV and STDs, and a world where women get the
reproductive health care they need without violence or harassment.
</P>
<P>
   Together, we will elect Al Gore, Joe Lieberman and a Democratic
Congress to keep faith with America's women and America's values.
</P>
<P>
   Together, we will make the right choice today and preserve our
choice for tomorrow.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-08-15-00 2133 </TRAILER>
