<DOCNO> APW20000815.0161 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-08-15 21:48 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> D-Backs' Guzman Leaves Game  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Arizona pitcher Geraldo Guzman mildly
sprained his left knee while stepping on a ball in Tuesday night's
game against Philadelphia and had to exit in the fifth inning.
</P>
<P>
   With two outs, Bobby Abreu hit a hard grounder back to the mound
that knocked Guzman's glove off. The ball caromed toward the first
base line and Guzman appeared to step on the ball with the back of
his left foot. The injury forced him to leave the game.
</P>
<P>
   Guzman will be reevaluated on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Guzman had allowed just three hits in four shutout innings
before getting into trouble in the fifth when he surrendered four
hits and four runs.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Morgan relieved and surrendered three straight RBI singles
to Scott Rolen, Travis Lee and Pat Burrell as the Phillies took a
5-3 lead.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
