<HEADLINE> Bisons 5, Buffalo 4 -- game 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OTTAWA (AP) - Talmadge Nunnari drove in three runs to lead the
Ottawa Lynx to a 5-4 win over the Buffalo Bisons in International
Baseball league action Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Brent Billingsley (8-8) pitched 5 2/3 innings to earn the win
for Ottawa in the first game of a double header. He allowed four
runs, walked three and struck out three.
</P>
<P>
   The game was shortened to 6&AMP;frac12; innings to accommodate both games.
</P>
<P>
   Guillermo Mota got the last out of the fifth and pitched a
perfect sixth for his seventh save of the season.
</P>
<P>
   Tim Drew (5-6) pitched a complete game for Buffalo in taking the
loss. He allowed ten hits, struck out five and walked three.
